        "created_at": "2020-06-07T01:57:53.218Z",
        "cooked": "<ol>\n<li>\n<p>The value of the watch will be checked after that trigger, and if it hasn\u2019t changed the watch won\u2019t fire.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>I think this gets bounced out to the client and probably automatically sent to the new location.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>I believe this can happen even if the watch is registered before any update, or at least it is allowed by contract.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
